  },
  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Ag Nutrient Solution Monitor\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Ag Nutrient Solution Monitor\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Monitors hydroponic nutrient solution quality including pH, electrical conductivity, and nitrogen concentration. Three concurrent patterns detect: pH acidification drift, EC toxicity escalation, and macronutrient deficiency. Upstream: raw nutrient sensors at [8:12]. Downstream: AgNutrientCycleOptimizer reads output at [28:32].\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- ph_norm (index 0):  0.0 = pH3 (extreme acid) | 0.5 = pH6.5 (optimal) | 1.0 = pH10 (extreme base)\n- ec_norm (index 1):  0.0 = 0 mS/cm (distilled) | 0.5 = 2.0 mS/cm (target) | 1.0 = 4.0 mS/cm (toxic)\n- nitrogen_norm (index 2):  0.0 = severe N deficit | 0.5 = optimal N level | 1.0 = N excess/toxicity\n- micronutrient_norm (index 3):  0.0 = severe deficit | 0.5 = balanced trace minerals | 1.0 = excess/lockout\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- PH_ALERT (AMBER) -> action: Inject pH-up solution; flush reservoir; notify nutrient cycle optimizer\n- EC_ALERT (AMBER) -> action: Add fresh water to reservoir; reduce nutrient dosing; flush substrate\n- DEFICIENCY_ALERT (AMBER) -> action: Add concentrated A+B nutrient solution; check dosing pump function",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "ph_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "pH3 (extreme acid)",
          "mid": "pH6.5 (optimal)",
          "high": "pH10 (extreme base)"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "ec_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "0 mS/cm (distilled)",
          "mid": "2.0 mS/cm (target)",
          "high": "4.0 mS/cm (toxic)"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "nitrogen_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "severe N deficit",
          "mid": "optimal N level",
          "high": "N excess/toxicity"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "micronutrient_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "severe deficit",
          "mid": "balanced trace minerals",
          "high": "excess/lockout"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "ag-nutrient-ph-drift",
        "label": "PH_ALERT",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "Inject pH-up solution; flush reservoir; notify nutrient cycle optimizer"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "ag-nutrient-ec-escalation",
        "label": "EC_ALERT",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 1,
        "action": "Add fresh water to reservoir; reduce nutrient dosing; flush substrate"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "ag-nutrient-deficiency",
        "label": "DEFICIENCY_ALERT",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 2,
        "action": "Add concentrated A+B nutrient solution; check dosing pump function"
      }
    ]
  },
  "agentBinding": {
